4
00:02:15,100 --> 00:02:15,540
Dude.

5
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:16,730
Hello.

6
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:18,670
Where is your village chief?

7
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,190
The village chief? He's over there.

8
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:21,990
Chief, someone is looking for you.

9
00:02:22,230 --> 00:02:22,670
Who is it?

10
00:02:22,870 --> 00:02:23,310
Chief.

11
00:02:24,829 --> 00:02:25,180
Chief.

12
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:26,230
Nice to meet you.

13
00:02:26,230 --> 00:02:26,630
Chief.

14
00:02:27,070 --> 00:02:27,790
You are...

15
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,920
I'm from Binhai Banxia Steel Co., Ltd.

16
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:30,550
Chen Yuzhou.

17
00:02:34,510 --> 00:02:34,950
What's the matter?

18
00:02:35,829 --> 00:02:36,310
Chief.

19
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:38,310
Does the mudflat in the west of the village

20
00:02:38,310 --> 00:02:39,190
belong to your village?

21
00:02:40,670 --> 00:02:42,110
I heard that

22
00:02:42,150 --> 00:02:43,450
it is for rent now, right?

23
00:02:44,350 --> 00:02:45,550
How do you want to rent it?

24
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:47,990
We just took a look.

25
00:02:48,820 --> 00:02:50,980
Its area should be about 4 hectares.

26
00:02:51,250 --> 00:02:52,329
We want to rent 2 hectares of it.

27
00:02:53,230 --> 00:02:53,870
Sure.

28
00:02:54,790 --> 00:02:56,430
How long will you rent it? What for?

29
00:02:56,670 --> 00:02:58,630
We plan to build a storage yard.

30
00:02:58,860 --> 00:02:59,790
What is a storage yard for?

31
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:01,560
Just for piling things,

32
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,510
like some scrap steel and scrap iron.

33
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,550
The tenancy should be at least five years, and 0.2 million yuan a year.

34
00:03:09,070 --> 00:03:10,110
We require one-off payment.

35
00:03:12,590 --> 00:03:13,150
Chief,

36
00:03:14,030 --> 00:03:15,910
could you please

37
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:16,990
lower the price a little bit?

38
00:03:17,490 --> 00:03:18,010
Let me tell you.

39
00:03:18,270 --> 00:03:19,780
Though we only rent 2 hectares for now,

40
00:03:20,230 --> 00:03:21,980
we also plan to build a wharf later,

41
00:03:22,030 --> 00:03:22,990
and will definitely rent a larger area of it

42
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,170
for many years.

43
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:26,220
We just entered the village.

44
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:27,630
The road is a bit awful.

45
00:03:28,030 --> 00:03:28,750
After we rent it,

46
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:30,110
we can build all the roads in your village

47
00:03:30,110 --> 00:03:31,110
into asphalt ones.

48
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:33,630
So, could you please lower the price?

49
00:03:34,070 --> 00:03:36,150
I didn't ask much from you.

50
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:39,230
Many companies want this land,

51
00:03:40,430 --> 00:03:41,750
like the provincial medical companies,

52
00:03:42,510 --> 00:03:43,270
and...

53
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:44,900
And...

54
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:46,710
many people have come to see it anyway.

55
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,230
If you really want to rent it, you have to hurry.

56
00:03:50,640 --> 00:03:51,670
Is your company state-operated?

57
00:03:53,110 --> 00:03:53,840
It's a private enterprise.

58
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:56,630
Self-employed?

59
00:03:57,340 --> 00:03:58,140
Not entirely.

60
00:03:58,310 --> 00:03:58,910
It's a company.

61
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,650
It's just not that big.

62
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,100
You plan to build a wharf?

63
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:04,030
It's a large scale.

64
00:04:04,310 --> 00:04:05,110
Don't worry.

65
00:04:05,550 --> 00:04:06,670
As long as you rent it to us,

66
00:04:06,670 --> 00:04:07,710
we will keep our promise.

67
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:12,710
Who are you?

68
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:13,920
Take out your cigarettes.

69
00:04:16,579 --> 00:04:18,380
Chief, I'm a businessman.

70
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,920
You? Running business here?

71
00:04:25,190 --> 00:04:26,120
About that mudflat,

72
00:04:26,470 --> 00:04:28,550
it was originally left for poultry raising.

73
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:30,790
And that's also some villagers' will.

74
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:32,430
So, we still need to hold a village meeting

75
00:04:32,990 --> 00:04:34,390
to discuss about whether to rent it out.

76
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:36,030
I can't decide it on my own.

77
00:04:39,110 --> 00:04:40,030
To rent it or not?

78
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:42,590
You can think about it.

79
00:04:45,110 --> 00:04:46,670
Okay, I understand.

80
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:49,270
Chief, we'll come back later.

81
00:04:53,990 --> 00:04:54,350
See you.

82
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:01,670
The village chief is definitely an old slick.

83
00:05:01,930 --> 00:05:03,150
You were too anxious.

84
00:05:05,520 --> 00:05:06,590
I was not.

85
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:09,310
Which eye of yours saw me being anxious?

86
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,470
Wait, I haven't said anything about you.

87
00:05:11,470 --> 00:05:12,550
Now are you even blaming me?

88
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:13,630
Listen.

89
00:05:14,190 --> 00:05:16,590
Can you prepare some good cigarettes from now on?

90
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:18,190
Nowadays, you have to look like a businessman.

91
00:05:19,670 --> 00:05:20,910
Was that about cigarettes?

92
00:05:21,940 --> 00:05:23,230
I don't know business.

93
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:25,190
But I can tell

94
00:05:25,550 --> 00:05:26,870
whether he's bad or not.

95
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:28,660
Let me tell you.

96
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:29,590
If you pretend to hesitate for a few days,

97
00:05:29,590 --> 00:05:30,550
he will definitely hurry to rent it.

98
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:33,750
You're getting more and more self-proud, aren't you?

99
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,390
You think I didn't notice it?

100
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:37,110
I knew he must be a sly guy

101
00:05:37,310 --> 00:05:38,670
at the first sight of him.

102
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:41,470
Fine, you're the smartest.

103
00:05:42,430 --> 00:05:43,980
What are you doing? Where are your manners?

104
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:44,620
Drive carefully.

105
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:36,310
How is it going?

106
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:39,100
What are you doing?

107
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:43,030
What are you doing here?

108
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:43,710
I didn't mean it.

109
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:45,510
Have the days in jail made you an idiot?

110
00:06:45,830 --> 00:06:46,870
Go watch movies.

111
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:49,460
Take it away.

112
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:50,890
I'm just afraid that it's too spicy for you.

113
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:52,750
Why do you add so much chili for noodles?

114
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,909
None of your business.

115
00:06:55,610 --> 00:06:57,090
Just some ledgers. Is it necessary to be this angry?

116
00:06:58,870 --> 00:06:59,830
You know nothing.

117
00:07:00,150 --> 00:07:00,790
Let me tell you.

118
00:07:00,810 --> 00:07:01,920
The ledger of Guo Qidong

119
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:03,630
is really made flawless.

120
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:05,310
If Qiu Bizheng finds it out,

121
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:06,340
he's gonna kill him.

122
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:08,970
What kind of friends are you making?

123
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,630
They don't look like good people at all.

124
00:07:11,030 --> 00:07:11,790
They look wicked.

125
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:13,150
You know nothing.

126
00:07:13,150 --> 00:07:13,870
This is business.

127
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:20,390
Hello.

128
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:21,640
Fatty.

129
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:23,550
Where are you?

130
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:26,060
Okay, I got it. Right away.

131
00:07:27,110 --> 00:07:27,870
Pack your things, quickly.

132
00:07:27,870 --> 00:07:28,350
Let's go.

133
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:28,910
Let's go out.

134
00:07:29,070 --> 00:07:29,550
For what business?

135
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:31,030
You'll know when you get there.

136
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,560
Put on your clothes. Let's go.

137
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:40,110
Here.

138
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:41,810
You have nothing to do here.

139
00:07:42,350 --> 00:07:44,150
Chen and I got you over a dozen trucks.

140
00:07:44,850 --> 00:07:45,690
They look battered,

141
00:07:46,310 --> 00:07:47,790
but should still work if repaired.

142
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:55,560
Boss.

143
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:57,909
I can't take them.

144
00:07:58,810 --> 00:08:00,640
You're in urgent need of money.

145
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:02,480
Don't worry about me.

146
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:03,910
I'll figure it out myself.

147
00:08:04,310 --> 00:08:05,150
Never mind,

148
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:06,790
we can still afford to these battered trucks.

149
00:08:07,450 --> 00:08:08,410
The construction of the storage yard is to start,

150
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:09,750
we have our own trunks.

151
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:10,590
We don't need to hire others.

152
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:12,990
In the future, you have to work on your own with your trucks

153
00:08:13,270 --> 00:08:14,870
and make some money for our company.

154
00:08:19,110 --> 00:08:20,710
No, I still can't take them.

155
00:08:22,110 --> 00:08:23,910
I'm not capable of managing so many trucks.

156
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:26,150
It costs a lot of money to repair them.

157
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,740
It's better for you to use them.

158
00:08:28,470 --> 00:08:28,900
Enough.

159
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:30,240
Stop pretending.

160
00:08:30,670 --> 00:08:31,270
This is your gift

161
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:33,390
from Fatty and me.

162
00:08:33,580 --> 00:08:35,100
Just take it.

163
00:08:37,730 --> 00:08:38,130
By the way,

164
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:40,600
be sure to get some good drivers.

165
00:08:41,070 --> 00:08:41,590
That's easy.

166
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,549
All of my buddies released from prison together with me can drive.

167
00:08:43,929 --> 00:08:45,370
We used to do this in jail.

168
00:08:45,550 --> 00:08:45,990
No.

169
00:08:46,580 --> 00:08:47,750
You can't contact those guys anymore.

170
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:48,830
Why?

171
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,200
Where can I find someone else?

172
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:54,750
Just hire some professional truck drivers.

173
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:56,190
I don't want you to have any connection

174
00:08:56,190 --> 00:08:57,150
with those guys.

175
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,040
What do you mean?

176
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,480
If you ask me to look for drivers,

177
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,270
then I definitely will contact my buddies.

178
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:04,120
Everyone I know has a criminal record.

179
00:09:04,470 --> 00:09:05,990
I don't know anyone without a criminal record.

180
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:06,670
I don't care.

181
00:09:06,870 --> 00:09:07,510
I just won't allow it.

182
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:08,430
Figure it out yourself.

183
00:09:09,830 --> 00:09:11,310
What's wrong with my buddies?

184
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:12,590
Besides,

185
00:09:12,590 --> 00:09:14,430
they had nothing to do with my going to jail.

186
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:22,270
What are you talking about?

187
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:24,230
Fatty,

188
00:09:24,590 --> 00:09:25,990
I think it's fine.

189
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:27,990
Just hire his buddies.

190
00:09:28,010 --> 00:09:29,790
Don't worry. I'll keep an eye on them.

191
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:30,480
It's okay.

192
00:09:34,620 --> 00:09:35,080
Apologize.

193
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,990
I didn't mean that.

194
00:09:43,430 --> 00:09:44,230
Forget it. I don't want the trucks.

195
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:45,580
Can you be more sensible?

196
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:49,630
Fatty, don't take it to heart.

197
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:50,830
He didn't mean that.

198
00:09:51,590 --> 00:09:52,670
That's what he meant.

199
00:09:55,050 --> 00:09:56,120
Can you be good?

200
00:10:05,070 --> 00:10:05,980
Can you be good?

201
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:10,670
I didn't mean that.

202
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,510
Don't take it to heart.

203
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:18,480
Later, remember to get licenses for the trucks.

204
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:20,230
Okay, no problem.

205
00:10:20,510 --> 00:10:21,110
Thank you, boss.

206
00:10:21,470 --> 00:10:23,040
Today is a big day for the Xiaoqi.

207
00:10:23,070 --> 00:10:23,830
Let's take a photo.

208
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:24,850
Big day?

209
00:10:25,270 --> 00:10:26,030
What big day?

210
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:27,230
Today

211
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:29,680
is a big day for you to start a good life.

212
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:31,950
Five seconds.

213
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:00,340
I just got a call from my friend.

214
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,200
It's said that the price of roll materials is very stable this year.

215
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:04,950
Why is your price

216
00:11:04,950 --> 00:11:05,660
so high?

217
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:07,030
Mr. Qiu,

218
00:11:07,870 --> 00:11:08,870
is this friend of you

219
00:11:08,870 --> 00:11:10,990
the Mr. Liu who just came from Guangzhou two days ago?

220
00:11:11,030 --> 00:11:11,540
Yes.

221
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:14,220
Those in Guangzhou

222
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:15,710
are indeed cold-rolled sheets imported from Japan.

223
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:17,630
And their price is actually 200 yuan less than ours.

224
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:20,050
But have you thought about why?

225
00:11:21,190 --> 00:11:22,350
You tell me, why?

226
00:11:22,730 --> 00:11:24,050
They have a large amount of the materials.

227
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:26,270
Don't take all of them out later.

228
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:27,620
Take whatever I tell you to.

229
00:11:27,950 --> 00:11:28,250
OK.

230
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:34,510
Our market is not satisfying this year.

231
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:35,880
Not only us.

232
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:36,750
It's the same condition for every company.

233
00:11:36,790 --> 00:11:37,990
Enough.

234
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,070
Who is it?

235
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:44,550
Mr. Qiu.

236
00:11:45,910 --> 00:11:46,510
Ms. Xu.

237
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:49,180
Why are you here?

238
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:51,150
You should have told me before coming here.

239
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:52,830
Mr. Guo is here too...

240
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,120
Since you're here,

241
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,160
you'd better stay.

242
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:57,420
Let's have dinner today.

243
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:58,410
Come, have a seat.

244
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,920
Go and order some dishes.

245
00:12:03,150 --> 00:12:04,900
Be sure to prepare both liquors and cold dishes.

246
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:05,940
Go now.

247
00:12:06,610 --> 00:12:08,040
I can ask Sun to do this.

248
00:12:08,510 --> 00:12:09,850
He usually does such things.

249
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:11,510
Why?

250
00:12:11,510 --> 00:12:12,510
You go in person.

251
00:12:12,630 --> 00:12:13,990
